Yes and no :)

If you make a class that does NOT inherit from monobehavior, you can still Serialize the class and use this class in another class that DOES inherit from monobehavior.

so if you have a class like this:

    [System.Serializable]
    public class ClassA
    {
    //you can add and access unity things, for example
    public Animator myAnimator;
    }

then in a class that inherits from monobehavior, you can use your class and see it in the instpector.

    public class ClassB : MonoBehavior
    {
    public ClassA myclass; //visible in the inspector.
    }

You can however NOT use things like &quot;GetComponent&quot;, that requires MonoBehavior.

